sql:
SELECT AVG(survey_count) AS average_voyages
FROM (
    SELECT COUNT(survey_id) AS survey_count
    FROM survey_logs
    GROUP BY participant_id
) AS participant_survey_counts;

external_knowledge:
- Finished surveys refer to surveys with a status of 'completed'.;
- The term 'answers given by participants' can be associated with the 'response_value' from the 'responses' table. ;
- The age group information is included to provide context to the responses, helping to understand the demographic of respondents.

